    "lp-completed": {
      "id": "lp-completed",
      "name": "Completed (47)",
      "parentId": "lp-root",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "type": "chapter",
      "content": "<p><strong>2026-06-05 / 2026-06-06 additions (see root for full detail):</strong> Reformat with AI feature + Discovery Hints system (two-tier dismissal + Professional mode) + outline search redesign (view-shaper, persistent state, AND-chain) + toolbar consolidation (-3 buttons via Quick Capture and Expand/Collapse merges, Refresh from Web relocation, Import as Chapter deletion, 5 orphan files removed) + responsive toolbar with overflow menu at 3 breakpoints + recursive Expand/Collapse fix + value-renames (Smart Tools / Quick Command / Ask Your Outlines / Refresh from Web) + tech stack canonicalization across 5 outlines + paste handler text-fidelity pivot + canonical \"publish\" procedure codified in operating procedures.</p><p></p><p><strong>2026-06-04 additions (see root for the shipped detail):</strong> #3 LIVE BOOKS live-refresh test, #4 Translate (re-mounted + wired), #5 Launch metrics dashboard, iOS stress-test exit affordance, YouTube import silent-failure fix, I/O toolbar buttons + Wrench slim, value-based naming pass (Smart Tools / Quick Command / Ask Your Outlines / Refresh from Web), cross-link Phase 1 (link node + click-to-jump), cross-link Phase 2 (sidebar nesting + multi-parent + loop indicator), durable operating procedures + user-level CLAUDE.md.</p><p></p><p><strong>Voice command UI hard pullback — DONE 2026-06-01.</strong> Typed natural-language input is now the default. Voice infrastructure preserved on disk but unreachable from the UI; future voice surface will be dictation/accessibility only, never command/control. (Commits c56c17b + dc1bc42.)</p><p><strong>Undo/redo regression fixed — DONE 2026-06-02.</strong> Three layered fixes: empty-input focus fall-through, pop-until-visible-change, and a suppressRedoClear window. Robustness suite went from 3/4 to 4/4. (Commit 810cebb.)</p><p><strong>Ollama installed-but-not-running UX — DONE 2026-06-03.</strong> Settings and Bulk Research dialogs now differentiate installed-but-not-running from not-installed, with new IPC handlers and a Start Ollama button. (Commit c7c7ffa.)</p><p><strong>Auth Phase 1 — DONE &amp; verified (#32).</strong> Tier model + env-gated Clerk auth layer. No-ops with no keys set; zero runtime cost until activated.</p><p><strong>Auth Phase 2 — DONE.</strong> Billing scaffolding: env-gated Stripe + RevenueCat, dormant until keys. Phase 3 (tier enforcement #33) still pending.</p><p><strong>LIVE BOOKS — BUILT &amp; shipped (#2).</strong> Generalized transform engine; documented in User Guide, Help Chat context, Help Chat API context, and How It Works outline. Core surface runtime-proven by a new automated Playwright test (#54): dialog, scope selection, preview, auto-apply-off, and merge-vs-overwrite all pass. Residual (medium follow-up #57): live AI refresh round-trip + post-refresh per-node diff cards not yet automation-covered.</p><p><strong>LIVE BOOKS automated test (#54) — DONE.</strong> Added to the Playwright suite; core surface verified runtime-working.</p><p><strong>Gemini 3.5 Flash switch — DONE (#49).</strong> Google I/O 2026 (2026-05-19) shipped Gemini 3.5 Flash, not a &quot;Gemini 4&quot;. The Gemini model registry is the single source of truth; the app-wide default now points at gemini-3.5-flash, with 2.5 Flash kept as a one-line rollback. Launch copy finalized in the soft variant (docs/launch/gemini-3.5-flash.md); the BYOK setup guide notes Google&#39;s ~55-day free-tier data retention.</p><p>Website updated &amp; live — stale March launch date removed, concrete role examples added.</p><p>Sentry crash reporting integrated across web, Electron, edge runtime. Free-tier safe. Needs a DSN from you to start collecting reports.</p><p>Accessibility audit (WCAG 2.1 AA). About 23 fixes applied — icon-only buttons got aria-labels, the outline now has proper ARIA tree semantics. Build clean.</p><p>Terms of Service draft. Marked DRAFT — needs lawyer review and a jurisdiction choice.</p><p>Refund Policy + dispute handling SOP. 14-day window, 3-day SLA, BYOK carve-outs documented.</p><p>App Privacy Nutrition Labels recommendation. Row-by-row answers ready for App Store Connect.</p><p>AI Consent reviewer documentation. Step-by-step for Apple App Review.</p><p>Incident Response + Backup/DR playbook. SEV ladder, scenario runbooks, post-mortem template.</p><p>Email deliverability setup guide. Resend + Google Workspace recommended. SPF/DKIM/DMARC steps.</p><p>Mac App Store decision: DMG-only for v1 (sandboxing would break Ollama, file access, MCP).</p><p>Sign in with Apple audit: not required — no auth exists today.</p><p>Launch announcement drafts: Product Hunt, Hacker News, Twitter, LinkedIn.</p><p>Beta tester + influencer outreach templates. Nick Milo (Linking Your Thinking) is the top target.</p><p>Knowledge Chat &quot;All Outlines&quot; test bug fixed. 38/38 tests passing.</p><p><strong>Auth provider — DECIDED 2026-05-26: Clerk.</strong> Lowest-friction path; the Phase-1 auth scaffolding already shipped is built around Clerk. Supports Sign In With Apple natively (required if we ever offer any third-party login on iOS per App Store guideline 4.8).</p><p><strong>Billing architecture — DECIDED 2026-05-26: RevenueCat orchestrating Apple IAP for v1; Stripe later via RevenueCat dashboard.</strong> iOS app legally must use Apple IAP for digital subscriptions (App Store 3.1.1). RevenueCat sits on top of Apple IAP and gives the app one entitlement API; free up to $2,500 MTR. When web payments matter later, Stripe plugs into RevenueCat without any app-code change — same entitlement API. Apple takes 30%/15% (Small Business Program); Stripe ~3% later.</p><p><strong>Tagline DECIDED 2026-05-26: \"The Premier Idea Developer.\"</strong> Headline + sub-headline + descriptive paragraph locked in. Sub-headline: \"Any idea. Any team, anywhere. Any language. AI at every step.\" A dedicated \"Built for globally distributed teams\" section sits directly under the hero with a concrete scene (Boston + Shanghai + São Paulo team collaborating in their native languages). Replaces the prior \"Build Your Second Brain\" hero. Both src/app/page.tsx and src/app/marketing/page.tsx updated to match.</p><p><strong>Pricing DECIDED 2026-05-26: 3-tier accessible structure.</strong> Free (BYOK; bring your own AI key for unlimited use), Student $4.99/mo (50% off, requires verification, 200 AI generations/month), Pro $9.99/mo or $89/year (save 25%; 1,000 AI generations/month, podcast + image generation, priority support). Replaces the prior 4-tier structure that had the $49.99 \"Academic\" tier (which was the opposite of accessible for students). Premium $29.99 tier removed for v1 — can be added back later as an upsell if telemetry shows demand. Marketing copy on both src/app/page.tsx and src/app/marketing/page.tsx updated.</p>",
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "1"
    },
    "lp-decisions": {
      "id": "lp-decisions",
      "name": "Waiting on your decisions (5)",
      "parentId": "lp-root",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "type": "chapter",
      "content": "<p><strong>1. Support email confirmation</strong> — support@2ndbrainware.com or something else? Affects refund policy, incident response, and customer-support setup.</p><p><strong>2. Status page vendor</strong> — pick a provider (e.g., Statuspage, Instatus, BetterStack) so the incident-response playbook can name a real surface for users to check during outages.</p><p><strong>3. Postgres provider</strong> — pick a managed Postgres host (e.g., Neon, Supabase, Railway, RDS) so backend persistence can be configured.</p><p><strong>4. Lawyer on call</strong> — choose the lawyer who will sign off on the Privacy Policy / Terms of Service drafts and be on call for incident-response and disputes.</p><p><strong>5. Legal jurisdiction</strong> — confirm the legal jurisdiction the company operates under so the TOS, Privacy Policy, and Refund Policy can name it explicitly.</p>",
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "2"
    },
    "lp-external": {
      "id": "lp-external",
      "name": "Waiting on external / user-only (10)",
      "parentId": "lp-root",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "type": "chapter",
      "content": "<p>Apple Developer cert ($99/yr) — verify account active, configure Team ID</p><p>Privacy Policy lawyer review — already drafted at /privacy, needs sign-off</p><p>Sentry DSN — create free Sentry account, paste DSN into Vercel env vars</p><p>Custom domain DNS — point 2ndbrainware.com (primary, matches support@ email) to Vercel; configure secondbrainware.com as a redirect-only domain to the primary</p><p>iOS TestFlight upload — needs your office / fast internet</p><p>Real-device test pass — Mac primary, then iPhone/iPad verification</p><p>Business infrastructure — LLC, bank account, Stripe Atlas entity, Google Play developer account</p><p>4 enterprise API responses — passive monitoring of inboxes</p><p>Customer support tooling pick — email-only, Help Scout, Front, etc.</p><p>OpenAI partnership form — complete the section OpenAI sent (they called you 2026-06-08); proactive partnership opportunity</p>",
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "3"
    },
    "lp-next": {
      "id": "lp-next",
      "name": "Next to tackle (P0 code work)",
      "parentId": "lp-root",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "type": "chapter",
      "content": "<p><strong>Status as of 2026-06-04 EOD:</strong></p><ul>\n<li><p><strong>#1 Auth Phase 3 tier enforcement (#33) — DONE.</strong> See Completed list.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>#2 BYOK API key entry UI (#34) — DONE.</strong> See Completed list.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>#3 LIVE BOOKS live-refresh test (#57) — DONE.</strong> See Completed list.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>#4 Language translation (#52) — DONE.</strong> See Completed list.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>#5 Launch metrics dashboard (#47) — DONE.</strong> See Completed list.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Remaining P0 code work:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>#6 Onboarding email sequence (#46).</strong> Welcome + 3-5 drip emails after signup. Copy-heavy.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>#7 Web payment / Stripe (#22).</strong> RevenueCat orchestration is wired; this completes the web-side billing UI. Needs Clerk + RevenueCat keys from Howard before going live.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Deferred to post-launch (v1.1):</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>Cross-link Phase 3.</strong> AI features (LIVE BOOKS, Translate, etc.) traversing link boundaries to operate across linked outlines. Substantial work; not launch-blocking.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Sidebar nesting refinements.</strong> Performance optimization, settings for multi-parent display, optional \"linked from X\" hint inline. After real user feedback informs choices.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Low-priority cleanup:</strong> test-screenshots relocation artifact (#55), flaky MCP search test (#56), ~115 pre-existing TS errors (#51).</p>",
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "4"
    },
    "lp-deferred": {
      "id": "lp-deferred",
      "name": "Post-launch / deferred (9)",
